Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The Uitenhage Lions Club cordially invites senior citizens to their 29th annual Senior Citizen s Christmas Supper treat.The service is provided to the elderly free of charge as a form of appreciation for their contribution to the advancement of the Uitenhage and Despatch communities during their economically active years.The supper includes a three course meal with light entertainment for ages 65 and older and we can only accept 180 elders for the event this year. All bookings will be dealt on a first come first served basis. It will be held at Woga (Old Moth Hall) on Monday, November 7th at 18:00. Bookings are essential. .24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.